About Us
Mobile Filter Notice
DATABASE RESULTS
Lake Highlander Resident Owned 55+ Mobile Home Park was established in 1990. Prior to being a mobile home park, the land was originally one of Florida’s many orange groves. Today our 293-unit park, which is nestled between established permanent housing communities, is a blend of permanent and seasonal residents who come from various locations throughout Canada and the United States. Upon arrival, seasonal residents look forward to their fun in the sun, seeing friends and neighbors, and participating in numerous community activities.
Lake Highlander 55+ Mobile Home Park offers:
A clubhouse, lending library, billiard and game room, geothermal heated pool, spacious lanai, laundry facility, shuffleboard courts, park office, and a beautiful lake.
Activities include golf, bowling, and shuffleboard leagues, social dinners and dances, bingo, game nights, exercise programs, organized outings, and weekly coffee hour.
Mission Statement
To provide a residential retirement environment, which is aesthetically pleasing, environmentally conscious, financially stable and well known in the community for our outstanding reputation.
Vision Statement
To be recognized as a premier mobile home retirement park on the gulf coast.
END DATABASE RESULTS
